---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Arizona Aikido – New Students">
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="border-b border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/90">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-8 md:py-14">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-violet-400">
        Start training
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-50">
        New Student Guide
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm md:text-base text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">
        New to Aikido or to Arizona Aikido? This page explains what Aikido is, what to expect in
        your first classes, and the basic etiquette we follow on the mat.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap">
        <a
          href="/schedule"
          class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-violet-500/70 bg-violet-600/90 px-4 py-2.5 font-medium text-slate-50 shadow-sm hover:bg-violet-500 sm:w-auto"
        >
          View class schedule
        </a>
        <a
          href="/cost"
          class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/80 px-4 py-2.5 font-medium text-slate-100 hover:border-slate-500 sm:w-auto"
        >
          See membership & costs
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <section
    class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-8 md:py-14 space-y-10 text-sm md:text-base text-slate-200 leading-relaxed"
  >
    <!-- What is Aikido -->
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">What is Aikido?</h2>
      <p>
        Aikido is a Japanese martial art that emphasizes balance, timing, and connection rather
        than strength or competition. Techniques use circular movement, body alignment, and
        redirection of force to neutralize attacks safely.
      </p>
      <p>
        Training includes falls and rolls (ukemi), throws, joint locks, and some weapons practice
        (wooden sword, staff, and knife). Practice is cooperative: partners work together so both
        people can learn.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Is this for me -->
    <section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">Is Aikido right for me?</h2>
        <p>
          Many people come to Aikido for self defense, fitness, stress relief, or simply because
          they enjoy learning movement and martial arts. You do not need to be flexible, strong, or
          in “perfect shape” to start.
        </p>
        <p>
          Training is adjusted to your level. New students focus on safe falling, posture, and basic
          movements long before anything advanced.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-emerald-500/40 bg-emerald-950/40 p-4">
        <h3 class="text-xs md:text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-300 uppercase tracking-[0.18em]">
          Good to know
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-emerald-100/90">
          <li>• No prior martial arts experience required.</li>
          <li>• You train at your own pace.</li>
          <li>• Instructors and seniors help you with basics.</li>
          <li>• Respect and safety are more important than strength.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- First class: what to expect -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">Your first class: what to expect</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Before class</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>• Arrive about 10–15 minutes early.</li>
            <li>• Remove shoes before stepping onto the mat area.</li>
            <li>• Let the instructor know you are new or visiting.</li>
            <li>• If you have injuries or limitations, tell the instructor.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">During class</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>• Class begins and ends with a bow and short moment of stillness.</li>
            <li>• The instructor demonstrates a technique.</li>
            <li>• Students pair up and practice the technique together.</li>
            <li>• Partners bow to each other before and after practicing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What to wear / bring -->
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">What to wear and bring</h2>
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base">
        For your first few classes you do <span class="font-semibold">not</span> need to buy a
        uniform immediately.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm md:text-base">
        <li>• Comfortable athletic pants (no shorts if possible) and a t shirt or long sleeve top.</li>
        <li>• Remove jewelry before training.</li>
        <li>• Bring water and a small towel if you like.</li>
        <li>• Later, you may want to purchase a white Aikido or judo gi (uniform).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Dojo etiquette -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">Dojo etiquette and safety</h2>
      <p>
        Etiquette is how we show respect for each other, the dojo, and the art. It may feel
        unfamiliar at first, but you will get used to it quickly by watching and asking questions.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="space-y-2 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Respect and bowing</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>• Bow when entering or leaving the mat area.</li>
            <li>• Bow to the instructor at the start and end of class.</li>
            <li>• Bow to your partner before and after practice.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">On the mat</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>• Try to arrive on time and be ready when class begins.</li>
            <li>• When the instructor is demonstrating, watch quietly.</li>
            <li>• If you are tired or dizzy, sit or kneel at the edge of the mat and rest.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm md:text-base font-semibold text-slate-100">Safety</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>• Tap or say “matte” if something feels painful or unsafe.</li>
            <li>• Do not force techniques on your partner.</li>
            <li>• Keep fingernails and toenails trimmed.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How classes work long term -->
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-50">How training works over time</h2>
      <p>
        As you continue, you will gradually learn breakfalls, core body movements, basic techniques
        from common attacks, and eventually weapons practice and more advanced material. Progress is
        marked through kyu and dan ranks, but the focus is steady improvement rather than
        competition.
      </p>
      <p>
        Senior students help newer students, and everyone trains together in a cooperative way. It
        is normal to feel awkward at first. Every instructor once felt the same.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Call to action -->
    <section class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-violet-600/40 bg-violet-900/20 p-6 space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-50">Ready to get started?</h2>
      <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-slate-200">
        The best way to understand Aikido is to feel it. You are welcome to visit the dojo, watch a
        class, or join in as a beginner.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap">
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-violet-500/70 bg-violet-600/90 px-4 py-2.5 font-medium text-slate-50 shadow-sm hover:bg-violet-500 sm:w-auto"
        >
          Contact the dojo
        </a>
        <a
          href="/directions"
          class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/80 px-4 py-2.5 font-medium text-slate-100 hover:border-slate-500 sm:w-auto"
        >
          Get directions
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
